e of crisis to characterize our times shows how this framing obscures the unjust conditions of existence and violence of everyday life. Together the essays in this book offer a fresh look at the deeply connected worlds we inhabit in solidarity and discord.Contributors. Banu Bargu, Veena Das, Alex de Waal, Didier Fassin, Peter Geschiere, Behrooz Ghamari-Tabrizi, Caroline Humphrey, Ravi Kanbur, Julieta Lemaitre, Uday S. Mehta, Jan-Werner Müller, Jonathan Pugh, Elizabeth F. Sanders, Todd Sanders  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLanguage and culture. 0aLanguage and languagesxPolitical aspects. 0aSociolinguistics. 0aWords, NewxPolitical aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aBargu, Banu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDas, Veena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDas, Veena, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDe Waal, Alex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFassin, Didier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFassin, Didier, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGeschiere, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhamari-Tabrizi, Behrooz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHumphrey, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanbur, Ravi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLemaitre, Julieta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMehta, Uday S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Jan-Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPugh, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4h